<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"In_psychology">In psycholog=
y</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLearning_c=
urve&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D1" title=3D"Edit section: In psycholog=
y"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:%C3%9Cber_das_Ged%C3%A4chtnis._Untersuchungen=
_zur_experimentellen_Psychologie,_Fig_2.png" class=3D"mw-file-description">=
<img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/%C3%9=
Cber_das_Ged%C3%A4chtnis._Untersuchungen_zur_experimentellen_Psychologie%2C=
_Fig_2.png/250px-%C3%9Cber_das_Ged%C3%A4chtnis._Untersuchungen_zur_experime=
ntellen_Psychologie%2C_Fig_2.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=
=3D"172" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"1243" data-file-heigh=
t=3D"853"></a><figcaption>Figure 2 from Ebbinghaus' <i>=C3=9Cber das Ged=C3=
=A4chtnis</i>. Ebbinghaus ran a series of 92 tests. In each test, he gave t=
he subject 8 blocks of 13 random syllables each, and plotted the average ti=
me taken for the subject to memorize the block.</figcaption></figure>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:%C3%9Cber_das_Ged%C3%A4chtnis._Untersuchungen=
_zur_experimentellen_Psychologie,_Fig_4.png" class=3D"mw-file-description">=
<img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ed/%C3%9=
Cber_das_Ged%C3%A4chtnis._Untersuchungen_zur_experimentellen_Psychologie%2C=
_Fig_4.png/250px-%C3%9Cber_das_Ged%C3%A4chtnis._Untersuchungen_zur_experime=
ntellen_Psychologie%2C_Fig_4.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=
=3D"101" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-width=3D"1392" data-file-heigh=
t=3D"564"></a><figcaption>Figure 4 from <i>=C3=9Cber das Ged=C3=A4chtnis</i=
>. The same test with 9 blocks of 12 syllables each. This shows an oscillat=
ing pattern.</figcaption></figure>
<p>Hermann Ebbinghaus' memory tests, published in 1885, involved memorizing=
 series of <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nonsense_syllable" clas=
s=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Nonsense syllable">nonsense syllables</a>, and r=
ecording the success over a number of trials. The translation does not use =
the term 'learning curve' =E2=80=94 but he presents diagrams of learning ag=
ainst trial number. He also notes that the score can decrease, or even osci=
llate.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ebbing_book_4-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"h=
ttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-ebbing_book-4"><span =
class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></=
sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-zimmer_3-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://=
en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-zimmer-3"><span class=3D"cit=
e-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=
=3D"cite_ref-7" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wik=
i/Learning_curve#cite_note-7"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>7<span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>The first known use of the term 'learning curve' is from 1903: "Brya=
n and Harter (6) found in their study of the acquisition of the telegraphic=
 language a learning curve which had the rapid rise at the beginning follow=
ed by a period of slower learning, and was thus convex to the vertical axis=
."<sup id=3D"cite_ref-books.google.com_5-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-books.google.com-5">=
<span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>5<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span>=
</a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-zimmer_3-2" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-zimmer-3"><span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>3<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Psychologist Arthur Bills gave a more detailed description of learni=
ng curves in 1934. He also discussed the properties of different types of l=
earning curves, such as negative acceleration, positive acceleration, plate=
aus, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ogive" title=3D"Ogive">og=
ive</a> curves.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-8" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https:=
//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-8"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>8<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"In_economics">In economics<=
/h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[=
</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLearning_cur=
ve&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D2" title=3D"Edit section: In economics">=
<span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span>=
</div>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"History">History</h3><span =
class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a =
href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DLearning_curve&amp;act=
ion=3Dedit&amp;section=3D3" title=3D"Edit section: History"><span>edit</spa=
n></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Learning_curve_cycle.png" class=3D"mw-file-de=
scription"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb=
/a/ae/Learning_curve_cycle.png/250px-Learning_curve_cycle.png" decoding=3D"=
async" width=3D"250" height=3D"158" class=3D"mw-file-element" data-file-wid=
th=3D"1600" data-file-height=3D"1014"></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure=
>
<p>In 1936, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Theodore_Paul_Wright" =
title=3D"Theodore Paul Wright">Theodore Paul Wright</a> described the effec=
t of learning on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Production_costs"=
 class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Production costs">production costs</a> in t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aircraft_industry" class=3D"mw-=
redirect" title=3D"Aircraft industry">aircraft industry</a> and proposed a =
mathematical model of the learning curve.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Wright,_T.P._1=
936_6-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learn=
ing_curve#cite_note-Wright,_T.P._1936-6"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</sp=
an>6<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 1952, the US Air Force published data on the learning curve in th=
e <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Airframe" title=3D"Airframe">air=
frame</a> industry from 1940 to mid-1945.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-9" class=3D"re=
ference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-=
9"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>9<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</sp=
an></a></sup> Specifically, they tabulated and plotted the direct man-hour =
cost of various products as a function of cumulative production. This forme=
d the basis of many studies on learning curves in the 1950s.<sup id=3D"cite=
_ref-10" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learn=
ing_curve#cite_note-10"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>10<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>In 1968 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruce_Henderson" ti=
tle=3D"Bruce Henderson">Bruce Henderson</a> of the <a href=3D"https://en.wi=
kipedia.org/wiki/Boston_Consulting_Group" title=3D"Boston Consulting Group"=
>Boston Consulting Group</a> (BCG) generalized the Unit Cost model pioneere=
d by Wright, and specifically used a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Power_Law" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Power Law">Power Law</a>, whic=
h is sometimes called <i>Henderson's Law</i>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-11" class=
=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite=
_note-11"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>11<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> He named this particular version the <b>experience cu=
rve</b>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-12" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-12"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>12<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-Grant2003_13-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-Grant2003-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[<=
/span>13<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
Research by BCG in the 1970s observed <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Experience_curve_effects" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Experience cur=
ve effects">experience curve effects</a> for various industries that ranged=
 from 10 to 25 percent.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-HaxMajluf_14-0" class=3D"referen=
ce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Learning_curve#cite_note-HaxMa=
jluf-14"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>14<span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
